{
  "stem": "16503.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was as a youth, everybody was allowed to take one suitcase, which was ridiculous because you never-- you know, what for?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But that was the, the propaganda.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they-- I, I want to go back to just one more point on Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, Red Cross has done tremendous things throughout the world, and I will acknowledge that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they came to Theresienstadt as a United Nation of some kind because I don't think United Nations was in existence in those years.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they came as a world unit to see how the Jews were treated in a ghetto in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, they did come.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The show, which was put on for them was unheard of.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Everything was painted.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The band in the square was playing music on the-- on the square.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were whisked through the streets.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were whisked to the-- to the children's home, but that was a children's home of younger kids, which eventually were all gassed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But those were like kindergarten kids.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And in front of the kindergarten kids-- and this is a true story-- were put sardines, and the children were taught to say, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The poor children didn't even know what the sardines were.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the Red Cross blew through it, and the sardines were bl-- taken away from the children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this was the inspection of the world of Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And it is absolutely unacceptable that the world was exposed because I am sure that there was on some kind of news reels somewhere being this shown.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And if that was shown and the delegation which was there accepted it for what they saw, I think it was a crime.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, we were-- we were allowed to walk the street.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
